## Lookup arguments

Specify exactly one of:

| argument | behavior |
|---|---|
| `id` | Direct lookup by integer ID. |
| `name` | Exact-match lookup by name (fuzzy server search, then exact `name ==` filter). Errors if zero or more than one model matches. |

## Returned values

| attribute | description |
|---|---|
| `id` | AI model integer ID. |
| `name` | Model name. |
| `model_provider` | Provider: one of `anthropic`, `azure_openai`, `bedrock`, `cohere`, `google`, `mistral`, `ollama`, `openai`, `openrouter`, `xai`. |
| `model_id` | Provider-specific model identifier (e.g. `claude-3-5-sonnet-latest`, `gpt-4o`). |
| `config` | Per-provider config JSON (sensitive). **Secret keys (`api_key` and any key named `secret`/`secret_key`/`token`/`password`/`access_key`) are masked as `***`** in this read — they cannot be recovered from the data source. |
| `is_default` | Whether this is the default model for agents. At most one model is default. |
| `created_at` | Creation timestamp. |
| `updated_at` | Last update timestamp. |

For the full shape of `config` per provider (which keys apply to which
`model_provider`, which are secret, and the stored-from-config secret-handling
rule), see the
[`mistershell_ai_model` resource](../resources/ai_model.md) page.
